    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <head>Translated parts</head>
                <p xml:id="KR3l0099-start">
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">and without blame.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Compiled by Gan Bao of Xincai, Attendant Gentleman of the Jin Dynasty, under the order of Ling Sheng.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Volume 1</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Shennong used a red whip to whip the hundred herbs,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">fully knowing their properties of neutrality, toxicity, coldness, and warmth,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">and what their smells and tastes were good for,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">in order to sow the hundred grains.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Therefore, the world called him Shennong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Chi Songzi (Master Red Pine) was</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">the rain master during the time of Shennong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">He took Bingyu Powder (Ice Jade Powder)</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">and taught it to Shennong.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">He could enter fire without being burned.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">He went to Kunlun Mountain,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">and often entered the stone chamber of the Queen Mother of the West,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">ascending and descending with the wind and rain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">A young daughter of Emperor Yan pursued him,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">also attained immortality,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">and they both left.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">During the time of Emperor Gao Xin,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">he again served as rain master,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">traveling among men.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">The present-day rain master is originally from him.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">Chi Jiangzi Yu (Master Red General Yu) was</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">a man of the time of the Yellow Emperor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">He did not eat the five grains,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">but ate the flowers of the hundred herbs.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">By the time of Emperor Yao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:24:14.304+09:00">he was a carpenter.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He could rise and fall with the wind and rain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He sometimes sold stringed arrows in the marketplace,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">so he was also called "Stringed Arrow Father."</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Ning Fengzi</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">was a man of the time of the Yellow Emperor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Tradition says he was the potter for the Yellow Emperor.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">A strange man passed by him</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">and was hired to manage the fire.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He could produce smoke of five colors.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">After a long time, he taught Fengzi this skill.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Fengzi accumulated fire and burned himself,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">and rose and fell with the smoke.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Examining his ashes,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">there were still bones.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">The people of that time buried him together in the northern mountains of Ning.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Therefore, he was called Ning Fengzi.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Wo Quan</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">was a medicine-gathering father from Huai Mountain.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He liked to eat pine nuts.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">His body grew hair,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">and he was seven inches tall.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">His eyes were square.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He could fly and chase running horses.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He gave pine nuts to Yao,</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">but Yao did not have time to eat them.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">The pine nuts</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">were from the Jian pine.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Those who took them</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">all lived three hundred years.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">Peng Zu</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">was a minister during the Yin dynasty.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">His surname was Qian</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">and his given name was Keng.</seg>
                    <seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-6a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#gemini-2.0-flash" modified="2025-05-08T09:25:34.624+09:00">He was a grandson of Emperor Zhuanxu.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
